# --------------------
# .gitignore for C# / .NET / ASP.NET Core projects
# Purpose: ignore generated/build/temp files while keeping everything
# required to clone and run the project on another machine.
# --------------------

# --------------------
#Short, crucial explanation (so others can run your project):
#	Do NOT ignore:
#		-	.sln, .csproj, .fsproj, .xproj — these must be committed.
#		-	appsettings.json — commit a non-sensitive default appsettings.json (or appsettings.Sample.json), so others have defaults. Ignore only development/local secrets files.
#		-	Migrations/ (EF Core) — commit migrations (so dotnet ef database update works).
#		-	package-lock.json / yarn.lock / pnpm-lock.yaml — commit lockfiles so front-end installs are reproducible.
#		-	Dockerfile / docker-compose.yml — commit so Docker-based runs work.
#	Use dotnet user-secrets for per-developer secrets instead of committing secrets files.
#	If your project needs a local DB file to run (rare for production), provide a sample DB or scripts and include instructions in README — don't commit real DB files.
# --------------------



# --------------------
# IDEs & Editors
# --------------------
# Visual Studio
.vs/
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates
*.VC.db

# Visual Studio Code
.vscode/*
# but allow workspace settings that you intentionally share:
# !.vscode/extensions.json
# !.vscode/settings.json
# !.vscode/tasks.json
# !.vscode/launch.json

# Rider / IntelliJ
.idea/
*.sln.iml

# ReSharper
_ReSharper*/
*.[Rr]e[Ss]harper



